baseName.value: Precast concrete segments for tunnel lining

generalComment.value:
The precast segments are still “Not yet in the market”, therefore the primary data collected in this study refers to production or representative products, referring to the year 2022.




Based on M3


"No cut-off elements were considered, therefore it is believed that the data represents at least 99% of the total flows (mass and energy) of phases A1, A2 and A3."

technologicalApplicability.value:
The precast concrete segments are elements used for cladding of hydraulic, railway and road tunnels dug into the ground with TBM (Tunnel Boring Machine) machines.
 "They are produced in reinforced concrete, with a structure designed to create complete rings which are progressively installed from the rear of the TBM, which gradually advances towards the excavation face.
Once a section of tunnel has been lined with prefabricated segments, it is used an injection mortar to solidify and consolidate the surrounding soil."
